<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="27.[189,400,1841,1867]" box="[189,400,1841,1867]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,400,1841,1867]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,400,1841,1867]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Brief description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[189,1399,1889,2025]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Monoecious. Primary or lower receptacle (below cells VI and VI’) consisting of 2–4(–5) superposed cells. Secondary stalk cell (VII) intercalary in the main axis of the thallus. Perithecial outer wall consisting of four vertical rows, each with many cells of similar length; two vertical rows of flattened cells alternating with two vertical rows of narrow elongated cells. Simple horns on perithecium.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
