</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[189,1399,312,375]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
The genus consists of 21 species. The most recently described species is 
<taxonomicName authority="(Santamaria 1999)" baseAuthorityName="Santamaria" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[1018,1394,312,339]" class="Laboulbeniomycetes" family="Ceratomycetaceae" genus="Ceratomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Laboulbeniales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="pyrenaeus">
<emphasis box="[1018,1171,313,339]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. pyrenaeus</emphasis>
(Santamaria 1999)
</taxonomicName>
, which is the only one known in Europe.
</paragraph>
